Scenario:
Refactor the previous Restaurant system to simplify the execution logic. In this version, the focus is on utilizing Java's functional capabilities or direct interface implementation to reduce boilerplate code.

Requirements:

Simplified Execution: Explore how to trigger cook() operations directly through a streamlined Waiter class without necessarily needing separate Command classes for every single action.

Polymorphism: Use the Meal interface as the primary contract for all cookable items.

Goal: Compare the traditional Command Pattern with a more direct polymorphic approach to understand the trade-offs between decoupling (Command) and simplicity (Direct Interface).